20:10.043 --> 20:11.936
KONSTANTIN: <i>These charges are absurd.</i>

20:11.937 --> 20:15.974
Once again,
you make Russia your bogeyman.

20:15.975 --> 20:18.243
No, that's all on you.

20:18.244 --> 20:21.746
CIA confirmed Canadian
Intelligence findings,

20:21.747 --> 20:23.948
so you can skip the denial.

20:23.949 --> 20:26.684
Our Treasury Department is preparing

20:26.685 --> 20:28.686
to levy retaliatory sanctions

20:28.687 --> 20:31.923
under Executive Order 13660.

20:31.924 --> 20:33.892
This is a serious escalation.

20:33.893 --> 20:36.294
I'm sorry, what?

20:36.295 --> 20:38.830
You infiltrated a peaceful protest

20:38.831 --> 20:41.299
and set off an antipersonnel bomb.

20:41.300 --> 20:43.968
And it is a miracle that no
one in the crowd was killed,

20:43.969 --> 20:45.970
including my son and his girlfriend.

20:45.971 --> 20:50.642
I didn't realize Jason
was at the conference.

20:50.643 --> 20:52.443
I can't imagine what you went through.

20:52.444 --> 20:53.878
No, you really can't.

20:53.879 --> 20:55.947
(SIGHS) And I could not have imagined

20:55.948 --> 20:57.315
inviting you back to the table

20:57.316 --> 21:00.351
after what you did,
but the planet can't wait.

21:00.352 --> 21:03.454
So you need to get serious
about negotiating.

21:03.455 --> 21:05.857
You may have bought Alaska,

21:05.858 --> 21:08.560
but the Arctic is in our blood.

21:08.561 --> 21:11.529
Your sanctions won't deter us.

21:11.530 --> 21:15.533
I'm glad your boy is okay.

21:15.534 --> 21:17.802
They've already been caught.

21:17.803 --> 21:19.203
What do they have to gain

21:19.204 --> 21:21.638
by continuing to obstruct?

21:23.041 --> 21:25.909
Blake, get me Ephraim Ware.

21:26.844 --> 21:31.015
I'm gonna put whatever
Intel assets we have

21:31.016 --> 21:34.618
in the Arctic on high alert
until we can find out.

21:35.320 --> 21:37.621
(ORGAN MUSIC PLAYING)

21:50.902 --> 21:52.570
Hope I'm not intruding.

21:52.571 --> 21:55.439
No, it's fine.

21:56.841 --> 21:59.410
How'd you find me?

21:59.411 --> 22:02.747
Former spy.

22:02.748 --> 22:05.583
Look, Andrew.
I can't accept your paper.

22:05.584 --> 22:08.518
I think you know why.

22:09.287 --> 22:11.287
Thought I'd give you
a chance to explain

22:11.288 --> 22:12.588
before I go to the commandant.

22:12.589 --> 22:14.590
I have no defense.

22:14.591 --> 22:16.292
You should do whatever
it is you have to do.

22:16.293 --> 22:17.927
Really?

22:17.928 --> 22:20.063
So no plea for leniency, no do-over?

22:20.064 --> 22:22.498
I have too much respect
for you, Dr. McCord.

22:22.499 --> 22:24.367
You're an ethical man.

22:24.368 --> 22:26.469
Yeah, that's the reputation I have,

22:26.470 --> 22:28.737
and you were counting
on that, weren't you?

22:29.472 --> 22:31.706
I don't know what you mean.

22:33.476 --> 22:35.745
Look, Andrew...

22:35.746 --> 22:38.181
at first I thought that in
addition to being lazy,

22:38.182 --> 22:39.882
you were also incredibly careless.

22:39.883 --> 22:41.351
But then I realized

22:41.352 --> 22:43.219
those two words
are the last I'd ever use

22:43.220 --> 22:45.288
to describe you.
You did it on purpose.

22:45.289 --> 22:48.056
I just don't know why.

22:50.760 --> 22:52.595
You know that poem by John Magee?

22:52.596 --> 22:54.097
"High Flight"?

22:54.098 --> 22:57.033
"Oh! I have slipped
the surly bonds of Earth

22:57.034 --> 22:59.802
and danced the skies
on laughter-silvered wings."

22:59.803 --> 23:01.269
Yeah. Why?

23:01.971 --> 23:04.407
Ever since I joined the Air Force,

23:04.408 --> 23:06.642
I was trained to kill.

23:06.643 --> 23:10.346
Simulations, training runs.

23:10.347 --> 23:12.615
You know it isn't real,

23:12.616 --> 23:15.118
and you tell yourself that maybe
by the time it is real,

23:15.119 --> 23:17.687
that it'll just feel automatic.

23:17.688 --> 23:19.689
Follow the orders.

23:19.690 --> 23:21.890
Fly home.

23:24.627 --> 23:27.430
The last lines of that poem,

23:27.431 --> 23:31.267
"And, while with silent,
lifting mind I've trod,

23:31.268 --> 23:33.102
"the high, untrespassed

23:33.103 --> 23:35.471
"sanctity of space,

23:35.472 --> 23:40.108
put out my hand
and touched the face of God."

23:43.312 --> 23:45.914
I feel like I've touched
the face of God.

23:46.649 --> 23:48.750
I can't do it.

23:50.486 --> 23:53.121
I can't kill.

23:54.857 --> 23:58.261
Yesterday you cited
Aquinas and just war.

23:58.262 --> 24:00.363
Killing in war
is different than murder,

24:00.364 --> 24:03.165
and, sadly, there are times
when it's necessary.

24:03.166 --> 24:04.771
I get that.

24:04.772 --> 24:07.036
And I thought that maybe
by taking that position,

24:07.037 --> 24:09.639
I could chase away my doubts.

24:09.640 --> 24:11.808
I'm not a pacifist, Dr. McCord,

24:11.809 --> 24:13.476
and I'm not afraid of dying,

24:13.477 --> 24:15.011
but I can't reconcile

24:15.012 --> 24:16.279
the questions you've been raising

24:16.280 --> 24:18.147
in class, and that made me realize

24:18.148 --> 24:20.216
that I can't live with the
guilt of taking a life.

24:20.217 --> 24:23.319
A civilian life. An innocent.

24:23.320 --> 24:26.021
Not even an enemy.

24:28.791 --> 24:30.793
Have you told your mom?

24:30.794 --> 24:34.897
My mom was chairwoman
of the Joint Chiefs.

24:34.898 --> 24:37.366
Now she's national security advisor.

24:37.367 --> 24:39.235
Service is everything to her.

24:39.236 --> 24:41.471
I can't.

24:41.472 --> 24:43.806
So rather than tell her,

24:43.807 --> 24:47.310
- you plagiarized your ethics paper.
- In the moment,

24:47.311 --> 24:49.879
it seemed like it was
better for her to believe

24:49.880 --> 24:52.115
that my career ended
over a lapse in judgment.

24:52.116 --> 24:53.616
I don't know how to tell her

24:53.617 --> 24:54.817
that this is my choice.

24:54.818 --> 24:56.552
Andrew, if there's one thing
I know about you,

24:56.553 --> 24:59.055
you're not a coward.

24:59.056 --> 25:01.324
There are things that you can do,

25:01.325 --> 25:03.759
steps to take.

25:03.760 --> 25:06.661
But your mom deserves
to hear about it from you.

25:10.533 --> 25:11.767
Petroleum, natural gas,

25:11.768 --> 25:14.170
and other fossil fuel innovations

25:14.171 --> 25:15.905
will be center stage right here.

25:15.906 --> 25:18.641
American geothermal,
solar, and wind companies

25:18.642 --> 25:20.376
will also be featured
in the annex here.

25:20.377 --> 25:21.844
More like broom closet.

25:21.845 --> 25:23.079
But still represented.

25:23.080 --> 25:24.747
By the way, I-I'm sorry
we didn't have time

25:24.748 --> 25:26.449
to make a new model, ma'am.

25:26.450 --> 25:28.684
No, I'm sorry

25:28.685 --> 25:31.654
that circumstances have
put us in this position.

25:31.655 --> 25:35.490
We need to be doing more
to fight climate change.

25:37.894 --> 25:40.730
But that's a great poster.

25:40.731 --> 25:43.099
Jay just called. Bella Rossi
is being released now.

25:43.100 --> 25:45.968
You mean actual not bad news?

25:45.969 --> 25:47.937
- Let's see it.
- (CROWD CHEERING OVER TABLET)

25:47.938 --> 25:50.306
BELLA: I would like to thank...
I would like to thank

25:50.307 --> 25:51.574
the U.S. Department of State,

25:51.575 --> 25:53.109
especially Chief of Staff Jay Whitman,

25:53.110 --> 25:54.977
for helping to secure my release.

25:54.978 --> 25:57.446
For any part my group
played in the violence

25:57.447 --> 26:00.181
at the summit, I am truly sorry.

26:01.851 --> 26:03.653
I cooperated with the authorities

26:03.654 --> 26:05.121
because I stand against violence,

26:05.122 --> 26:08.090
but silence is not a
condition of my freedom.

26:08.091 --> 26:11.260
We will never stop denouncing
the corporations and governments

26:11.261 --> 26:14.130
who continue to suppress
the truth about global warming

26:14.131 --> 26:15.798
- and continue to poison the planet.
- What is she doing?

26:15.799 --> 26:17.833
- She was just supposed to apologize.
- Well, you can lead

26:17.834 --> 26:20.670
- an activist to an apology...
- (PHONE RINGING)

26:20.671 --> 26:22.838
Until we end our addiction
to oil and gas,

26:22.839 --> 26:24.373
future generations will suffer

26:24.374 --> 26:26.013
unimaginable flooding,
pollution, and poverty.

26:26.014 --> 26:28.511
Hello. Please hold.
Ma'am, Chip Harding

26:28.512 --> 26:29.812
would like a word.

26:29.813 --> 26:31.614
CHIP: <i>I sponsored</i>

26:31.615 --> 26:34.250
the expo to boost my image,
and what do I hear?

26:34.251 --> 26:37.153
Bella Rossi name-checking
your chief of staff

26:37.154 --> 26:39.021
while she trashes my business.

26:39.022 --> 26:41.891
We assist all citizens,

26:41.892 --> 26:44.060
regardless of their perspectives.

26:44.061 --> 26:45.394
Yeah, try telling that to my board.

26:45.395 --> 26:46.495
My inbox is filling up

26:46.496 --> 26:48.798
with some very unhappy perspectives.

26:48.799 --> 26:51.033
I want a public statement of support

26:51.034 --> 26:52.668
for drilling in the Arctic Circle.

26:52.669 --> 26:55.304
The administration
has taken no such position.

26:55.305 --> 26:56.672
Well, it's about to.

26:56.673 --> 26:58.174
With no drilling, there's no gas.

26:58.175 --> 26:59.342
With no gas, there's no future.

26:59.343 --> 27:01.477
Your company has been saying that

27:01.478 --> 27:03.346
for 30 years, Chip,

27:03.347 --> 27:06.582
and it is as false now as it was then.

27:06.583 --> 27:09.385
Yeah, well, the money's just as green,

27:09.386 --> 27:10.819
so what's it gonna be?

27:12.989 --> 27:16.158
Chip Harding is no longer our sponsor.

27:16.159 --> 27:17.226
MAN: What did I say?

27:17.227 --> 27:18.327
Because of Bella Rossi?

27:18.328 --> 27:22.064
Because I refused to endorse
Arctic drilling.

27:22.065 --> 27:23.399
(OVERLAPPING CHATTER)

27:23.400 --> 27:24.667
And I may also

27:24.668 --> 27:28.437
have mentioned
his company's long history

27:28.438 --> 27:31.040
of hiding data
and denying climate change.

27:31.041 --> 27:32.808
(OVERLAPPING CHATTER) And violating

27:32.809 --> 27:34.610
the Foreign Corrupt Practices Act,

27:34.611 --> 27:36.912
so that probably did it.

27:36.913 --> 27:37.947
That explains it.

27:37.948 --> 27:39.681
I like your style.

27:44.220 --> 27:46.555
Andrew filed for Class O-1.

27:46.556 --> 27:49.691
Permanent change in status.

27:50.493 --> 27:52.962
I know how much
his service meant to you.

27:52.963 --> 27:55.498
"There are things you can do,
steps to take."

27:55.499 --> 27:56.932
Did you really tell him that?

27:56.933 --> 27:58.801
Yes.

27:58.802 --> 28:00.069
Knowing where it would lead.

28:00.070 --> 28:02.872
- Ellen, he followed his conscience.
- No.

28:02.873 --> 28:04.874
He's in the thrall
of his ethics professor,

28:04.875 --> 28:07.575
- and you're going to talk him out of it.
- I can't do that.

28:10.413 --> 28:12.281
When he was six,

28:12.282 --> 28:15.084
he begged to quit karate.

28:15.085 --> 28:18.054
Said he didn't want to hurt
any other kids.

28:18.055 --> 28:21.424
Then he won state title. Twice.

28:21.425 --> 28:23.359
Your class...

28:23.360 --> 28:25.328
You've turned him into a philosopher,

28:25.329 --> 28:26.629
and that might be fine

28:26.630 --> 28:28.130
for an ethics professor,

28:28.131 --> 28:31.233
but it is not the job
of a fighter pilot.

28:31.234 --> 28:34.236
- Ellen...
- Please.

28:34.237 --> 28:37.439
If anyone can change his mind,
it's you.

28:45.439 --> 28:48.175
Okay, before we start,

28:48.176 --> 28:49.910
I just want to say
that this whole thing,

28:49.911 --> 28:52.179
the whole...

28:52.180 --> 28:55.949
Canada hotel underage sexcapade thing

28:55.950 --> 28:57.818
is all Piper's deal,

28:57.819 --> 28:59.286
and nothing even happened.

28:59.287 --> 29:01.121
You know, and even if you hadn't
walked in when you did, Mom,

29:01.122 --> 29:02.923
nothing would have happened, anyway,

29:02.924 --> 29:04.391
because Piper freaked out.

29:04.392 --> 29:06.927
And-and now she's ghosting me,

29:06.928 --> 29:08.729
so still nothing's happening.

29:08.730 --> 29:10.897
And so I...

29:10.898 --> 29:12.966
think I've learned my lesson,
so good talk.

29:12.967 --> 29:15.234
Sit down.

29:18.438 --> 29:20.440
(SIGHS) I told you everything.

29:20.441 --> 29:21.675
What do you want from me?

29:21.676 --> 29:24.010
We want you to acknowledge
that you conned your mom

29:24.011 --> 29:26.379
into taking you and your
girlfriend to a foreign country

29:26.380 --> 29:28.248
while she was on official
government business

29:28.249 --> 29:30.250
so you could sneak into
Piper's hotel room.

29:30.251 --> 29:32.452
Which we paid for, by the way.

29:32.453 --> 29:35.122
Yeah. Not only did you deceive us

29:35.123 --> 29:37.124
but also the Boroumands,
who are trusting Mom

29:37.125 --> 29:38.592
to chaperone their daughter.

29:38.593 --> 29:40.260
And...

29:40.261 --> 29:42.596
I-I totally understand that.

29:42.597 --> 29:44.431
Okay? But...

29:44.432 --> 29:47.434
have you guys even thought that
if we did go to the protest...

29:47.435 --> 29:49.136
which we were gonna do, by the way,

29:49.137 --> 29:51.037
because she was gonna do
her interview after...

29:51.038 --> 29:53.306
then...

29:53.307 --> 29:55.108
maybe we would have
died in the explosion.

29:55.109 --> 29:57.477
- I don't know, okay? I...
- Are you really gonna go there, pal?

29:57.478 --> 29:59.479
Come on.

29:59.480 --> 30:01.047
(SIGHS)

30:01.048 --> 30:02.649
Every second she won't talk to me,

30:02.650 --> 30:04.651
it's like a dagger in my heart.

30:04.652 --> 30:06.553
So...

30:06.554 --> 30:09.189
I don't know why you
guys expect me to be...

30:09.190 --> 30:11.124
thinking straight right now.

30:11.125 --> 30:13.326
So...

30:13.327 --> 30:18.197
innocent by reason
of love-induced insanity?

30:18.965 --> 30:21.734
(PHONE BUZZING)

30:23.270 --> 30:24.471
You gonna get that?

30:24.472 --> 30:27.374
No.

30:27.375 --> 30:28.809
(BUZZING CONTINUES)

30:28.810 --> 30:30.076
Mom.

30:30.077 --> 30:32.078
If it's important, they'll get me.

30:32.079 --> 30:35.515
In two days, Jason, I haven't heard

30:35.516 --> 30:40.854
anything even resembling an apology.

30:40.855 --> 30:42.856
You need to take responsibility
for your actions.

30:42.857 --> 30:45.958
You're right.

30:46.893 --> 30:48.328
(SIGHS)

30:48.329 --> 30:50.163
I'm sorry.

30:50.164 --> 30:52.632
I'm sorry I lied to you.

30:52.633 --> 30:55.601
I really messed up.

30:56.369 --> 30:59.004
(DOORBELL RINGS)

31:00.974 --> 31:03.776
(SIGHS)

31:07.581 --> 31:09.716
Listen,

31:09.717 --> 31:13.220
- Piper is just...
- (ELIZABETH SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY)

31:13.221 --> 31:15.355
she's upset and embarrassed.

31:15.356 --> 31:18.325
And... she'll get over it.

31:18.326 --> 31:19.759
It's just gonna take her some time.

31:19.760 --> 31:21.561
She'll call you
when she's ready. Okay?

31:21.562 --> 31:23.864
- Come on.
- Okay.

31:23.865 --> 31:26.565
And everything you're
feeling is normal, okay?

31:26.566 --> 31:27.434
(SIGHS)

31:27.435 --> 31:29.601
Thanks so much, Frank.

31:32.405 --> 31:33.672
(SIGHS)

31:34.474 --> 31:36.376
Is he all right?

31:36.377 --> 31:38.945
Yeah. He'll be writing
bad poetry in no time.

31:38.946 --> 31:40.413
But we still need to punish him.

31:40.414 --> 31:42.449
We will. But I got to get to the...

31:42.450 --> 31:45.751
emergency NSC meeting.

31:46.453 --> 31:48.188
Bye.

31:48.189 --> 31:50.489
Bye. Good luck with Ellen.

31:54.160 --> 31:56.830
Ellen.

31:56.831 --> 31:59.032
Listen, I-I, uh...

31:59.033 --> 32:01.167
I'm sorry about Andrew.

32:01.168 --> 32:03.703
You should feel sorry
for our military.

32:03.704 --> 32:06.740
Countless hours of instruction,

32:06.741 --> 32:09.276
the millions spent on training,

32:09.277 --> 32:10.343
and it's all for nothing.

32:10.344 --> 32:13.213
I-I, I think you're wrong about that.

32:13.214 --> 32:14.981
Young man like Andrew,

32:14.982 --> 32:17.516
he'll find a way to make his mark.

32:18.218 --> 32:22.022
Sometimes these kids that we love

32:22.023 --> 32:24.223
make decisions we don't.

32:27.494 --> 32:28.929
Ellen.

32:28.930 --> 32:30.563
Bess.

32:30.564 --> 32:32.432
It's worse than we thought.

32:32.433 --> 32:34.367
WARE: Per our conversation,

32:34.368 --> 32:38.004
we concentrated intelligence
assets in Eastern Russia.

32:38.005 --> 32:40.106
That's how we learned
their Northern Fleet

32:40.107 --> 32:42.776
secretly left base
in Kamchatka an hour ago.

32:42.777 --> 32:44.577
Six destroyers, four frigates,

32:44.578 --> 32:46.513
and three next-gen
icebreaker corvettes

32:46.514 --> 32:49.282
armed with Kalibr
anti-ship cruise missiles.

32:49.283 --> 32:51.017
All on a direct course
for the Chukchi Ridge.

32:51.018 --> 32:52.185
ELIZABETH: It's a...

32:52.186 --> 32:53.687
region of dispute at the summit.

32:53.688 --> 32:55.522
PARKER: They're escorting
the <i>Kaliningrad,</i>

32:55.523 --> 32:57.257
a mobile offshore base

32:57.258 --> 32:59.025
with potential to stay
on station for months.

32:59.026 --> 33:01.428
We're looking at an occupation.

33:01.429 --> 33:03.930
Explains why they bombed the summit.

33:03.931 --> 33:06.266
They wanted to strike while
all the other Arctic powers

33:06.267 --> 33:07.334
were still divided.

33:07.335 --> 33:10.470
Sir, this fleet is a
clear and present danger

33:10.471 --> 33:12.005
to the people of Alaska,

33:12.006 --> 33:13.974
and not to mention a brazen violation

33:13.975 --> 33:16.109
- of international law.
- I agree.

33:16.110 --> 33:18.178
If the Russians are allowed
to claim the Chukchi Ridge,

33:18.179 --> 33:21.081
they could dominate the Arctic
for the next hundred years.

33:21.082 --> 33:23.116
Options?

33:23.117 --> 33:25.185
The Third Fleet is
a day's steam to the south.

33:25.186 --> 33:27.687
But without icebreakers,
there's no way

33:27.688 --> 33:29.155
it reaches the disputed zone in time.

33:29.156 --> 33:30.957
HILL: The <i>Polar Star's</i> in dry dock.

33:30.958 --> 33:32.792
The <i>Healy's</i> in the Southern Ocean.

33:32.793 --> 33:34.160
What about our allies?

33:34.161 --> 33:35.462
They'll never get there in time.

33:35.463 --> 33:37.897
ELIZABETH: There is one

33:37.898 --> 33:41.133
"near-Arctic" power that can help us.

33:43.169 --> 33:45.538
Madam Secretary,
I share your distress,

33:45.539 --> 33:49.409
but China has no military
vessels in the Chukchi Sea.

33:49.410 --> 33:54.547
Well, the <i>Xue Long 3</i> is 30 miles
north of Saint Paul Island.

33:54.548 --> 33:57.751
Yes, with a pod of our beloved orcas.

33:57.752 --> 34:00.887
Did you know they only sleep
with one hemisphere

34:00.888 --> 34:02.555
of their brain at a time?

34:02.556 --> 34:04.157
I did not.

34:04.158 --> 34:05.759
Such inquisitive creatures.

34:05.760 --> 34:08.728
Yet we have much to learn from them.

34:08.728 --> 34:10.030
Ming,

34:10.031 --> 34:13.900
the Russians are mere hours
from claiming the Arctic.

34:13.900 --> 34:15.568
What a shame.

34:15.569 --> 34:17.637
But our mission is peaceful.

34:17.638 --> 34:21.007
Is that why
your marine biologists are armed

34:21.007 --> 34:23.143
with Yu-6 torpedoes

34:23.143 --> 34:25.945
and C-803 cruise missiles?

34:25.946 --> 34:29.882
Elizabeth, I don't see
how we can help.

34:29.884 --> 34:30.884
You said it yourself.

34:30.885 --> 34:32.518
China is not an Arctic power.

34:32.520 --> 34:36.822
It's... simple geography.

34:37.623 --> 34:39.626
Name your price.

34:39.627 --> 34:41.661
DALTON: <i>So now China's</i>

34:41.661 --> 34:42.929
in the Arctic Council.

34:42.929 --> 34:45.565
With full voting power,
not that we had a choice.

34:45.565 --> 34:47.167
But will Russia play along?

34:47.168 --> 34:49.002
Only if they blink first.

34:49.003 --> 34:51.303
DALTON: What's the sitrep?

34:52.072 --> 34:54.174
Captain Prosky, report.

34:54.175 --> 34:55.742
Sir, thanks to the <i>Xue Long 3,</i>

34:55.743 --> 34:57.410
we've been able to set
an intercept course

34:57.411 --> 34:58.478
for the Russian fleet.

34:58.479 --> 34:59.813
Have we warned 'em off?

34:59.814 --> 35:01.714
Yes, but they're ignoring our calls.

35:01.715 --> 35:03.216
They're not backing down.

35:03.217 --> 35:05.452
Russian jets have already
buzzed our ships at close range.

35:05.453 --> 35:07.353
How long do we have, Captain?

35:07.354 --> 35:09.322
Their anti-ship missiles
should be in range

35:09.323 --> 35:12.225
of our aircraft carrier
in less than three minutes, sir.

35:12.226 --> 35:13.504
What about countermeasures?

35:13.505 --> 35:15.662
The <i>Wayne Morris</i> has the
SSDS Mark II system,

35:15.663 --> 35:17.897
but if even one
of those missiles gets through,

35:17.898 --> 35:20.133
there are 5,000 sailors aboard ship.

35:20.134 --> 35:22.902
And in these waters, they'll die
of exposure in minutes.

35:22.903 --> 35:24.838
HILL: Forget battle losses.

35:24.839 --> 35:27.006
If there's a naval engagement
with Russia,

35:27.007 --> 35:28.942
it could lead to retaliation
in Europe.

35:28.943 --> 35:31.244
Salnikov would never let it
get that far,

35:31.245 --> 35:33.179
not with China involved.

35:33.180 --> 35:35.081
Call again, Captain.

35:35.082 --> 35:37.550
Russian Commander,
this is Captain Joseph Prosky

35:37.551 --> 35:38.618
of the U.S. Navy.

35:38.619 --> 35:41.454
Your occupation of this sector
is illegal

35:41.455 --> 35:42.755
under international law

35:42.756 --> 35:45.358
and a violation
of American sovereignty.

35:45.359 --> 35:47.360
Heave to and alter course.

35:47.361 --> 35:49.561
This is your final warning.

35:53.433 --> 35:55.668
Fire one across her bow.

35:55.669 --> 35:57.270
- C.I.C.
- Aye, sir.

35:57.271 --> 35:58.938
PROSKY: Fire one five-inch shell
across her bow.

35:58.939 --> 36:01.241
OFFICER: Firing.

36:01.242 --> 36:04.443
(WHOOSH)

36:09.015 --> 36:11.250
They're not turning.

36:13.653 --> 36:16.189
One minute until missile range.

36:16.190 --> 36:18.557
Your orders, sir?

36:27.939 --> 36:29.045
PARKER: 30 seconds

36:29.046 --> 36:30.710
- until missile range.
- HILL: Mr. President,

36:30.711 --> 36:32.978
I recommend moving to DEFCON 2.

36:34.714 --> 36:36.915
Do it.

36:38.184 --> 36:40.186
Get me NORAD.

36:40.187 --> 36:42.222
Russian radar is locked.
They're lighting us up.

36:42.223 --> 36:43.489
We need a decision, sir.

36:47.360 --> 36:48.995
Mr. President?

36:48.996 --> 36:50.397
Pull back, Captain.

36:50.398 --> 36:51.398
Get out of there.

36:51.399 --> 36:52.899
Disengage and deploy from theater.

36:52.900 --> 36:56.369
CSG-3, I repeat, disengage.

36:56.370 --> 36:57.570
OFFICER: Aye, sir.

36:57.571 --> 36:58.939
They're turning.

36:58.940 --> 37:00.208
The Russians are turning.

37:00.209 --> 37:01.509
Belay that order, Captain.

37:01.510 --> 37:03.378
- Belay, belay, belay.
- The Russian fleet is bugging out.

37:03.379 --> 37:06.080
CSG-3, belay and resume course.

37:06.081 --> 37:08.950
I repeat, resume course.

37:08.951 --> 37:11.319
I ordered a retreat.

37:11.320 --> 37:12.954
Was that the right call?

37:12.955 --> 37:15.523
With thousands

37:15.524 --> 37:18.359
of lives at stake...

37:18.360 --> 37:20.660
Honestly, I don't know.

37:21.396 --> 37:23.663
(GRUNTS)

37:24.499 --> 37:28.636
My father was a sergeant
with the 6th Armored

37:28.637 --> 37:31.906
when they liberated Buchenwald.

37:31.907 --> 37:33.541
(SCOFFS, CLICKS TONGUE)

37:33.542 --> 37:37.243
His generation fought
for something existential.

37:38.045 --> 37:39.780
We just played chicken
with the Russians

37:39.781 --> 37:42.216
over a slice of frozen wasteland

37:42.217 --> 37:44.452
that spends six months
of the year in total darkness.

37:44.453 --> 37:47.755
The world is changing rapidly.

37:47.756 --> 37:50.324
We're all just struggling to keep up.

37:50.325 --> 37:51.425
Yeah.

37:51.426 --> 37:53.094
Teaming up with the Chinese.

37:53.095 --> 37:54.061
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

37:54.062 --> 37:56.564
Have to admit, I did
not see that coming.

37:56.565 --> 37:59.734
You know what I can't
get out of my head?

37:59.735 --> 38:02.303
That Chinese icebreaker

38:02.304 --> 38:05.539
can push through 20-foot-thick ice

38:05.540 --> 38:08.876
at seven knots for two years

38:08.877 --> 38:10.277
before refueling.

38:10.278 --> 38:11.245
And you know why?

38:11.246 --> 38:14.348
Because it runs on nuclear power.

38:14.349 --> 38:17.451
We let a transformative,

38:17.452 --> 38:19.987
carbon-free technology

38:19.988 --> 38:22.790
get buried in fear

38:22.791 --> 38:24.925
and ignorance.

38:24.926 --> 38:28.729
And now we're suffering
the consequences.

38:28.730 --> 38:33.834
It doesn't have the clarity
of battle lines on a map,

38:33.835 --> 38:38.539
but climate change is the
existential threat of our time.

38:38.540 --> 38:43.978
And we have to do more
than provide moral leadership.

38:43.979 --> 38:46.947
You want to revisit
our nuclear energy policy.

38:46.948 --> 38:48.182
I do.

38:48.183 --> 38:51.118
And I know exactly where to start.

38:51.119 --> 38:53.554
The CDF is still worried
about the threat of a meltdown.

38:53.555 --> 38:55.356
JAY: That threat has
always been way overblown,

38:55.357 --> 38:56.390
if nonexistent.

38:56.391 --> 38:57.922
And barring some technical moon shot,

38:57.923 --> 39:00.127
which isn't going to happen,
we are not getting

39:00.128 --> 39:03.731
to 100% renewables
before the ice caps are gone.

39:03.732 --> 39:05.199
Between us,

39:05.200 --> 39:08.269
I get that modern nuclear plants

39:08.270 --> 39:11.605
using light-water reactors
are virtually accident-proof.

39:11.606 --> 39:14.642
Then what's with all the "bathe
the planet in radiation" stuff?

39:14.643 --> 39:15.643
Official party lines.

39:15.644 --> 39:16.911
Our members,

39:16.912 --> 39:18.512
they think any support of nuclear

39:18.513 --> 39:21.148
- takes money away from renewables.
- So educate them.

39:21.149 --> 39:22.699
It's not that simple. I need
to think about my donor base.

39:22.700 --> 39:25.086
Actually, it is.

39:25.087 --> 39:27.521
I need to fight global warming,

39:27.522 --> 39:29.356
and I cannot do that without them.

39:29.357 --> 39:31.125
You can't win that fight
without nuclear power.

39:31.126 --> 39:32.426
ELIZABETH: And we can't sell

39:32.427 --> 39:34.028
the public without you.

39:34.029 --> 39:36.497
So sponsor our pavilion
at the World Expo.

39:36.498 --> 39:37.998
BLAKE: Admittedly,

39:37.999 --> 39:39.266
it's a stripped-down version.

39:39.267 --> 39:40.601
ELIZABETH: But one that will showcase

39:40.602 --> 39:42.269
a future where carbon-based fuels

39:42.270 --> 39:45.038
are actually a thing of the past.

39:45.806 --> 39:47.807
(SIGHS)

39:48.509 --> 39:50.344
HENRY: <i>Lieutenant Hill was raised</i>

39:50.345 --> 39:52.046
to join the family business.

39:52.047 --> 39:54.648
He loves flying. He loves flying

39:54.649 --> 39:57.785
more than anything in the world,

39:57.786 --> 40:00.054
and he would never
willingly give it up

40:00.055 --> 40:01.822
unless he had no choice.

40:01.823 --> 40:04.458
He never wanted to be a
conscientious objector.

40:04.459 --> 40:06.560
He wanted to be a fighter pilot.

40:06.561 --> 40:08.762
But he knows that

40:08.763 --> 40:10.564
his participation
in the death of others

40:10.565 --> 40:12.967
would leave him with a
guilt he couldn't bear,

40:12.968 --> 40:16.437
a-a moral wound from which
he would never recover.

40:16.438 --> 40:17.972
He's heartbroken that he let down

40:17.973 --> 40:21.876
his commanding officers
and his loved ones, but...

40:21.877 --> 40:23.310
he is determined to serve this country

40:23.311 --> 40:24.545
in ways outside the military,

40:24.546 --> 40:26.614
and I have every confidence
he'll find a way

40:26.615 --> 40:27.915
to do that.

40:27.916 --> 40:30.050
I believe that Lieutenant Hill's

40:30.051 --> 40:31.719
motives are pure,

40:31.720 --> 40:34.522
and I support his application

40:34.523 --> 40:36.624
for conscientious objector status.

40:36.625 --> 40:39.226
Thank you, Dr. McCord.

40:39.227 --> 40:41.527
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

40:55.075 --> 40:56.810
Hey.

40:56.811 --> 40:59.280
- Hi.
- Where is everyone?

40:59.281 --> 41:03.017
Mom wanted to have dinner
at, uh, Mazzarella's

41:03.018 --> 41:06.587
to celebrate her new partnership
with the Climate Defense Force.

41:06.588 --> 41:08.455
<i>Viva la nuclear.</i>

41:08.456 --> 41:10.157
Ah, indeed.

41:10.158 --> 41:12.726
- Ali is taking one for the team.
- Mm.

41:12.727 --> 41:15.829
And I got out of it
by playing the work card.

41:15.830 --> 41:17.598
As you can see.

41:17.599 --> 41:19.433
I thought you were having
dinner at Piper's.

41:19.434 --> 41:21.401
I did, too.

41:22.469 --> 41:24.471
What happened?

41:24.472 --> 41:26.640
Um...

41:26.641 --> 41:28.941
she broke up with me.

41:30.211 --> 41:32.512
What?

41:33.214 --> 41:36.083
Jason.

41:36.084 --> 41:38.719
I'm so sorry.

41:38.720 --> 41:41.055
I just...

41:41.056 --> 41:42.189
(SIGHS)

41:42.190 --> 41:43.357
I just don't get it, you know?

41:43.358 --> 41:44.925
Like... (SIGHS)

41:44.926 --> 41:47.928
last week she wanted to take our
relationship to the next level

41:47.929 --> 41:49.395
and now she's ending it?

41:50.164 --> 41:51.999
Yeah.

41:52.000 --> 41:55.336
(SIGHS) I mean...

41:55.337 --> 41:59.873
I don't know...
if-if relationships made sense,

41:59.874 --> 42:03.444
I would've been married,
like, three times by now.

42:03.445 --> 42:05.746
That doesn't make any sense.

42:05.747 --> 42:08.349
Exactly.

42:08.350 --> 42:10.351
Aw.

42:10.352 --> 42:12.353
God.

42:12.354 --> 42:14.355
(EXHALES)

42:14.356 --> 42:16.622
(CLICKS TONGUE)

42:18.926 --> 42:20.928
(SIGHS)

42:20.929 --> 42:23.564
How do I make the pain go away?

42:23.565 --> 42:26.566
You kinda don't.

42:27.635 --> 42:30.371
You just got to wallow in it

42:30.372 --> 42:33.706
for as long as it takes.

42:36.677 --> 42:38.178
Well, this sucks.

42:38.179 --> 42:39.847
(CHUCKLES)

42:39.848 --> 42:41.814
I know.

